                        <td>
                        <font class = headline>Timing: Mez vs. charm</font><br>
                        <IMG
                            SRC="Not Used"
                            BORDER="0"
                            ALIGN="RIGHT" HSPACE="20" VSPACE="10">
                       <font size = 2 face = arial color = black>Posted by: necrro</font><br> 
                       <font size = 1 face = arial color = black>Posted on: Mon Jul  1 21:54:10 2002</font><br><br> 
                       You all know that certain classes can mezz and/or charm creatures. (ENCs anything; Druids animals; necros mezz anything, charm undead; Bards anything).<br><br>Did you know that except for Bard's mez/charm ability which is dependent on their song, all mezzes have a set duration you can time using a stopwatch.<br><br>Did you also know that Charms vary in duration from one tick to full duration for that spell.<br><br>When you are in a group and mezz breaks on a mob, someone broke it. If mezz sticks the first time, it stays for the full duration of the spell unless broken. So no matter what anyone says about not hitting that mobs, etc., someone broke mezz. Charm is simply variable. No way to know how long it will last.<br><br><br>Some facts about various mezzes. Necro mezz is called Screaming Terror lasts 18 seconds. ENC mezzes (they have the largest line of mezzes) can last from 18 seconds up to almost a minute and a half. AoE mezzes always last a shorter time than an equivalent level single target mezz. Enc's get both kinds. If your Enc is not using his or her AoE mezz, it is primarily due to mana vs. mezz time consderations. AoE mezzes also suck a lot of mana. Single target mezzes are cheaper and last longer. Additionally, ENC's dont like AoE mezzes for large groups (I have mezzed up to 8 mobs at once in Karnors) because they all break at the same time and guess who they are coming after if you did not mem wipe them. If mana is not a problem, AoE mezzes are preferrable because you do not have to worry about targetting.<br><br>Just remember, when in a group with a mezzing Enc., using the assist button is key. Additionally, do not help the Enc if mezz breaks unless they ask. Encs have a spell line that allows them to control pesky mobs so they may be re-mezzed. Your assistance will only prevent re-mezzing and likely get the Enc killed.<br><br> 
                       Necrro 53rd Heretic (Misty Knight)<br>
                       <img src = "/beta/_necrro/_necrro/portrait.gif

" width = 50 height = 60><br>
